Phase 2 of the cage lifecycle: stands up the API proxy for billed modes, execs the caged process via `bwrap`, and stops the proxy afterward. Entry point is `run_until_exit(r: &Resolved, prep: &Prep) -> Result<RunOutcome, CageError>`.

The proxy runs on a background thread (`start_proxy`) bound to a Unix socket at `prep.rundir/API_SOCK_NAME`; it's only started when `mode_is_billed(&r.mode)` is true. Auth is passthrough — the caged claude's own OAuth header goes straight to `api.anthropic.com`; no key is injected here (`api_key: None`). After the cage exits, the proxy is stopped via an `AtomicBool` flag and joined; a proxy failure (panic or error) is folded into a capped diagnostic string (`proxy_diagnostic`) but never fails the overall run — a transient proxy hiccup shouldn't sour an otherwise-good billed session (ADR-027). Diagnostic is read from the run dir's `proxy.log` before `execute` calls `teardown_run`, since the file disappears after.

Inside the cage, a `socat` relay is launched on `127.0.0.1:8080` (`RELAY_PORT`) forwarding to the bind-mounted proxy socket; `wait_for_relay_snippet` blocks (up to 5s) until that listener actually shows `LISTEN` in `/proc/net/tcp`, avoiding an ECONNREFUSED race with claude's first request. It deliberately checks `/proc/net/tcp` rather than opening a real probe connection, because `socat ...,fork` would forward any accepted connection (even an empty probe) into the host proxy, producing a spurious "EOF before request head" log line on every startup.

`exec_cage` builds `bwrap` args via `crate::bwrap::build_bwrap_args` and either runs on a PTY (interactive mode, via `pty::run_on_pty`) or via `Command::new("bwrap")`. Interactive mode uses `setsid --ctty --wait` so claude gets a controlling terminal from its own PTY slave stdin — omitting this causes Node's readline to busy-spin at 100% CPU in the PID namespace.

`cage_cmd_for_mode` dispatches per `Mode`: `SelfTestStub` runs a containment self-check shell script (`self_test_stub_cmd`) verifying workspace writability, secret masking (masked files must still be *readable-as-empty*, not error — a prior mask design broke git), git functionality, and no network egress, writing only under `target/` (ADR-027, cwd-relative per ADR-046). `Task`/`Interactive` run `claude_cmd`, which wires up the relay + wait snippet + `exec claude ...`.

Couples tightly to `crate::bwrap` (arg format, `API_SOCK_NAME`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`), `crate::proxy` (`ProxyConfig`, `SocatUpstream`, `serve` signature), and `super::env`/`super::prepare::Prep` for run-dir layout — changes to any of those must stay in sync with usage here. Submodule `pty` handles PTY allocation for interactive mode; `tests` covers this file's logic.